genresAdvancedInfo.name: bhutanese pop
genresAdvancedInfo.description: Bhutanese pop is a genre of music that originated in the small Himalayan kingdom of Bhutan. It is characterized by its use of traditional Bhutanese instruments, such as the dranyen and the chiwang, as well as modern pop elements. Bhutanese pop is known for its upbeat and lively rhythms, and its lyrics often explore themes of love, friendship, and the beauty of nature.
